{"session_id":"svc-1778977550664517091","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-17T00:25:51.532945931Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"opus","sticky":{"key_present":true,"assignment":"not_applicable","bonus":0},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"resolved_harness":"claude","harness_source":"auto_route","resolved_model":"opus","work_dir":"/var/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-fizeau-80d4bf41-20260517T002546-88bc61c5","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead in an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the contract: every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Too big if any holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across ~5+ files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, use a split-first pass.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, children once more; reject third-level splits with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child (copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;`.\u0026#xA;4. Write `no_changes_rationale.txt` under the bead metadata `bundle` path with child IDs, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Decomposition alone is success. Do not mix it with implementation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC to concrete evidence (test, file, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Run git/index mutations sequentially; do not use parallel tool calls for `git add`, `git commit`, or other staging/commit commands.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- If `lefthook run pre-commit` depends on staged files, rerun it after staging the exact commit set. A `no-staged-files` run is not acceptance evidence.\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- Current-bead lifecycle is orchestrator-owned. Do not run `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --claim`, `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --status \u0026lt;status\u0026gt;`, `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --unclaim`, or `ddx bead close \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;`. Step 0 still allows `ddx bead create`, `ddx bead dep add`, and `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;`.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `no_changes_rationale.txt` under the bead metadata `bundle` path before exiting. No commit or rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The `no_changes_rationale.txt` file under the bead metadata `bundle` path must contain one of:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;cmd\u0026gt;` — repo cwd; exit 0 closes, nonzero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: open` + `reason: \u0026lt;retryable\u0026gt;` — open, smart retry.\u0026#xA;- `status: proposed` + `reason: \u0026lt;operator needed\u0026gt;` — operator lane.\u0026#xA;- `status: blocked` + `reason: \u0026lt;external blocker\u0026gt;` — blocked lane.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;No pseudo-statuses. Bare rationales and `status: needs_investigation` are rejected.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;For orchestrator decomposition, add `orchestrator_action: decompose` alongside `status: open`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Reports go under the bead metadata `bundle` path in `.ddx/executions/`. **Never write reports to `/tmp` or outside the repo**. Use a named in-repo path when given; otherwise write `\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md` there. Commit it with the code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Mode and overrides\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DDX_MODE=bead_execution: edit code/docs for bead AC. Only broad queue-steward default is overridden; tracker, merge-policy, verification, safety stay active. Bead description/AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and defaults.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other instruction files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"fizeau-80d4bf41\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003eauto-route: enumerate per-tier candidates for multi-tier subscription harnesses (claude opus/sonnet/haiku)\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;Under policy=default (auto-route mode, no --harness/--provider/--model pin), Fizeau collapses each subprocess harness to ONE scoring candidate — its DefaultModel. Multi-tier subscription harnesses like claude (which advertises sonnet/opus/haiku as siblings under one auth) therefore only ever offer their default tier to the auto-route scorer. Sonnet and haiku can never win on cost vs opus even though the catalog has full power/cost metadata for all three.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Concrete symptom from downstream DDx caller: every policy=default dispatch lands on claude/opus-4.7 because internal/harnesses/registry.go:51 sets DefaultModel=\u0026#34;opus-4.7\u0026#34;. For a 2207-token implementation prompt at role=implementer, opus won score 100.5. When the same dispatch is rerun with --model sonnet-4.6 pinned, sonnet scores 196.0 — it would have beaten opus by 95.5 points if it had been enumerated.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Cost gap is material: opus is 5x sonnet on input tokens, ~5x on output (cost_input_per_m: 15.0 vs 3.0; cost_output_per_m: 75.0 vs 15.0 per internal/modelcatalog/catalog/models.yaml). A project running ddx work continuously is defaulting every dispatch to the most expensive tier.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE (tentative — pointers, not patch)\u0026#xA;service_routing.go:1172-1189 (auto-route candidate add loop):\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;    for _, h := range entries {\u0026#xA;        if h.DefaultModel != \u0026#34;\u0026#34; {\u0026#xA;            add(h.DefaultModel, true, status)      // adds opus-4.7 for claude\u0026#xA;        }\u0026#xA;        for _, modelID := range h.SupportedModels {\u0026#xA;            add(modelID, true, status)              // SHOULD add sonnet-4.6 too\u0026#xA;        }\u0026#xA;        ...\u0026#xA;    }\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;subprocessHarnessModelIDs(\u0026#34;claude\u0026#34;, cfg) at service_models.go:91-101 returns the full [\u0026#34;sonnet\u0026#34;, \u0026#34;sonnet-4.6\u0026#34;, \u0026#34;opus\u0026#34;, \u0026#34;opus-4.7\u0026#34;, \u0026#34;claude-sonnet-4-6\u0026#34;] set. So sonnet SHOULD be reaching the candidate pool. Evidence says it does not — three candidate causes I could not disambiguate without deeper reading of routing.Inputs construction:\u0026#xA;1. Downstream aggregation/dedup is keeping one model per {harness, provider} key (picking DefaultModel as representative).\u0026#xA;2. Eligibility map keyed by modelID at ~line 1170 is collapsing sonnet entries by family before the candidate list is emitted.\u0026#xA;3. h.SupportedModels is being populated empty at the call site that builds entries (different from the metadata_billing.go:71 path).\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The routing_decision event is unambiguous: no sonnet row at all in the candidates array, not even excluded. A row with eligible:false, filter_reason:... would be diagnostic; silent absence is consistent with \u0026#34;never enumerated.\u0026#34;\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;CATALOG IS NOT THE GAP\u0026#xA;internal/modelcatalog/catalog/models.yaml has complete sonnet-4.6 metadata: power 8 (vs opus 10), cost_input_per_m 3.0, cost_output_per_m 15.0, surfaces include agent.anthropic:sonnet-4.6 and claude-code:sonnet-4.6. This rules out the power_missing exclusion path (the one that drops openrouter/anthropic/claude-haiku-4.5 with filter_reason: \u0026#34;power_missing\u0026#34;).\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;SECOND BUG SURFACED BY THE REPRO\u0026#xA;Pinning --model sonnet-4.6 routes through fiz/openrouter (catalog\u0026#39;s openrouter_id), NOT through the claude subscription harness. So pinning by model name does not produce a same-harness alternative tier even when one exists on the same auth. The openrouter route then fails 401 because no auth header is configured. So the workaround \u0026#34;pin sonnet by name\u0026#34; doesn\u0026#39;t actually deliver sonnet on the claude subscription path; it falls back to a separate per-token provider.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX (direction, not prescriptive)\u0026#xA;For multi-tier subscription harnesses, enumerate one candidate per tier (opus, sonnet, haiku) with each tier\u0026#39;s catalog power/cost, all routing through the same harness. Let cost-aware scoring pick the cheapest tier that meets power_hint_fit for the prompt. Today the harness behaves like \u0026#34;one model, take it or leave it\u0026#34;; it should behave like \u0026#34;one auth, multiple tiers.\u0026#34;\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If aggregation-by-harness is intentional for some other reason, the alternative is to make the harness configurable to expose multiple DefaultModels per role/power-band, and have callers pass a power hint that selects the right one.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;REPRO\u0026#xA;1. Configure Fizeau with the claude harness (subscription path, no model pin).\u0026#xA;2. Send any execute request with policy=default, no --harness/--provider/--model.\u0026#xA;3. Inspect the routing_decision event — only claude/opus-4.7 appears under claude; no sonnet, no haiku.\u0026#xA;4. Resend with --model sonnet-4.6. Route goes to fiz/openrouter/anthropic/claude-sonnet-4.6 with score 196.0 (not to the claude subscription path), and fails 401 if openrouter is not authed.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;CALLER CONTEXT\u0026#xA;DDx CLI on main branch at commit 09881f3a5. DDx does not pre-resolve routing knobs (per CONTRACT-003 / FEAT-010) and passes policy=default through verbatim. Verified by grep: no routing_decision/power_hint_fit/score_components emitter in DDx — only in github.com/easel/fizeau@v0.12.2.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;- The openrouter 401 (separate Fizeau config issue: that route needs an auth header configured).\u0026#xA;- DDx-side changes; ddx work is doing the right thing per contract.\u0026#xA;- Catalog metadata additions (sonnet-4.6 metadata is already complete).\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;CROSS-REF\u0026#xA;Github issue: https://github.com/easel/fizeau/issues/6 (mirrors this bead for external visibility).\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. Under policy=default with no --model pin, a claude subscription harness produces multiple candidates in routing_decision.candidates: one per available tier (at minimum opus-4.7 and sonnet-4.6; haiku if catalog has it). Verified by integration test that dispatches a default-policy request and asserts \u0026gt;1 claude candidate.\u0026#xA;2. Each per-tier candidate carries the correct power and cost from internal/modelcatalog/catalog/models.yaml (sonnet=8, opus=10), and each routes to the same harness (claude), not via fiz/openrouter fallback.\u0026#xA;3. For a 2000-3000-token implementation prompt at role=implementer with policy=default, sonnet-4.6 beats opus-4.7 on score under default scoring weights (cost_input_per_m: 3 vs 15 dominates the cost component). Verified by a deterministic scoring test or a snapshot of the routing_decision event with the chosen tier asserted.\u0026#xA;4. Pinning --model sonnet-4.6 against the claude subscription harness routes through the claude harness (not fiz/openrouter). Verified by a test that sets up a claude harness mock and asserts dispatch destination.\u0026#xA;5. The routing_decision event for any excluded same-harness tier carries an explicit filter_reason — silent absence of a candidate row is forbidden when the tier is known to the catalog. Verified by negative test: artificially break sonnet-4.6\u0026#39;s catalog metadata and assert it appears with filter_reason:\u0026#34;power_missing\u0026#34; (or similar) rather than vanishing.\u0026#xA;6. cd /Users/erik/Projects/fizeau \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./... green.\u0026#xA;7. No regression in existing routing tests (service_adr005_test.go, service_routing_test.go, internal/routing tests).\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003cnotes\u003e\ndecomposed into fizeau-f7fa1d87 (engine: enumerate per-tier candidates for multi-tier subscription harnesses in default policy), fizeau-59df1d15 (routing: pin --model sonnet-4.6 routes through claude subscription harness, not openrouter fallback), fizeau-b11da788 (routing: emit filter_reason for excluded same-harness tier — no silent absence). Splits the 7 ACs across three subsystem-focused children: engine enumeration + per-tier cost (1,2,3 of parent); model-pin→subscription-harness preference (4); observability/filter_reason invariant (5). ACs 6,7 (green tests, no regression) apply to each child.\n    \u003c/notes\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ekind:bug, area:routing, area:harness, impact:cost, evidence:downstream-ddx, refs:github-issue-6, ac-quality:needs-refinement\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata base-rev=\"be700493025f7c8e750eba18153b6ec38be9473e\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260517T002546-88bc61c5\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cnote\u003eNo governing references were pre-resolved. The bead description above is the primary contract. If it names files, specs, or prior beads, read them first. Ground decisions in repository state; do not guess.\u003c/note\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"DDX_MODE":"bead_execution","GIT_CONFIG_GLOBAL":"/var/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-fizeau-80d4bf41-20260517T002546-88bc61c5/.ddx/executions/20260517T002546-88bc61c5/embedded/git-global.cfg","GIT_CONFIG_SYSTEM":"/dev/null","PATH":"/var/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-fizeau-80d4bf41-20260517T002546-88bc61c5/.ddx/executions/20260517T002546-88bc61c5/embedded/git-bin:/usr/local/cuda/bin:/home/erik/.jbang/bin:/home/erik/.opencode/bin:/home/erik/.local/share/mise/installs/bun/1.3.11/bin:/home/erik/.local/share/mise/installs/node/22.21.1/bin:/Users/erik/.antigravity/antigravity/bin:/home/erik/bin:/home/erik/.local/share/mise/shims:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/home/erik/.local/bin:/home/erik/bin:/home/erik/.dotfiles/git-subrepo/lib:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/Applications/SnowSQL.app/Contents/MacOS:/home/li